ðŸ§© The 4 Two-Pointer Patterns (ONLY THESE)

1ï¸âƒ£ Slowâ€“Fast (Filter pattern)

Use when:
1. Remove / move / compress elements
2. Maintain order

Examples:
1. LC 283 (Move Zeroes)
2. LC 26 (Remove Duplicates)

Template:-

slow = 0
for fast in array:
    if valid:
        arr[slow] = arr[fast]
        slow++

2ï¸âƒ£ Leftâ€“Right (Sorted array)

Use when:
1. Array is sorted
2. Pair / sum / comparison

Examples:
LC 167, LC 15

Template:-

l = 0, r = n-1
while l < r:
    if condition:
        l++
    else:
        r--

3ï¸âƒ£ Sliding Window (Subarray / substring)

Use when:
1. Continuous range
2. Count / frequency

Examples:
LC 1358, LC 992

Template:-

for right:
    add(right)
    while invalid:
        remove(left)
        left++

4ï¸âƒ£ Two Windows (Exact K)

Use when:
1. Exactly K something

Examples:

LC 992, LC 1248
